1. Ja sam odlučio da *povučem* svoju ponudu za kupovinu kuće. (I decided to *withdraw* my offer to buy the house.)
2. Ona se brzo *povukla* kada je shvatila da je pogrešila. (She quickly *retreated* when she realized she was wrong.)
3. Ova traka se može lako *povući* da bi se otvorio poklopac. (This strip can be easily *pulled* to open the lid.)
4. Uspeli smo *da povučemo* korene iz ove stare biljke. (We managed *to extract* the roots from this old plant.)
5. On je *povukao* teške terete tokom celog svog života. (He *carried* heavy loads throughout his life.)
6. Moramo *da se povučemo* iz ovog projekta jer nema dovoljno resursa. (We have to *withdraw* from this project because there are not enough resources.)
7. Ova haljina se *povlači* iz prodaje jer ima fabričku grešku. (This dress is *being recalled* because it has a factory defect.)
8. Trebalo bi *da se povučemo* i da ponovo razmislimo o našoj strategiji. (We should *retract* and reconsider our strategy.)
9. On je bio primoran *da povuče* svoju tužbu nakon što se dogovorio sa optuženim. (He was forced *to withdraw* his lawsuit after he reached an agreement with the accused.)
10. Ponekad je najbolje *povući* se i pričekati da se situacija smiri. (Sometimes it's best *to retreat* and wait for the situation to calm down.)